BENIN – The National Directorate of Employment (NDE), on Monday in Benin city opened a five-daytraining programme for women in the production of Organic products, including Perfumery, Gele tying, Event management and Tie and Dye. Mallam Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo, NDE Director-General, while declaring the programme open said the Skills Acquisition training for 130 unemployed women was being carried out under the women Employment Branch (WEB) of the Small Scale Enterprises. He said the Directorate will also be training women on trends in the fashion industry which is aimed at creating wealth and generating employment opportunities. -Advertisement- Fikpo who was represented by Mr Edobor Solomon, Edo State Coordinator, noted that NDE is gender sensitive, hence the latest programme kick-starts the training of women in Natural organic products, including stone/bead making, Perfumery, as well as Tie and Dye. This, he said, was geared towards boosting the economy of the participants and increasing the Country’s export rate. According to him, a total of 130 women are being trained in this programme which is geared towards equipping Edo Women with the desired demand—driven skills to become self-reliant and future employers of Labour. Welcoming the participants, Edo State Coordinator, Mr Edobor Solomon, pointed out that the programme seeks to remedy the Social imbalance particularly, Skills gap among unemployed women in the state. The programme, according to Edobor, is aimed at helping Women Acquire Skills to enable them increase their income-generating activities for sustainability, improved Socio-Economic Status of women, reduce poverty and create wealth.Also speaking, the HOD Small Scale Enterprises (SSE) Mrs. Vivian Okosun appreciated the NDE management for approving the training of women to be held in Edo State.